subsection.p:
For
\mathbf F=(P,Q,R),
\boxed{\oint_{\partial S}\mathbf F\cdot d\mathbf r=\iint_S(\nabla\times\mathbf F)\cdot\widehat{\mathbf n}\,dS.}

Classically:
\boxed{\iint_S(\nabla\times\mathbf F)\cdot\widehat{\mathbf n}\,dS=0}
for a closed oriented surface, provided \mathbf F is smooth near S.
